<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1049,1336]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="563">
1. Body and legs brown (
<figureCitation box="[449,506,1049,1071]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,519,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1428,519,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Amazobenna reticulata Penny: 1. Male habitus, lateral view; 2. Female, habitus, lateral view; 3. Male head, anterior view; 4. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Male antenna, lateral view; 6. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 1= 1mm; 2,4 = 0.5mm; 3 = 0.3 mm; 5 = 0.4 mm. Specimen from Amazonas, Manaus, highway AM 010, Km 54." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632445/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); wing with brown spot in the costal cell, spots at the apex of the medial veins interconnected basally (
<figureCitation box="[307,380,1079,1101]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,1618,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[188,1398,1618,1955]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28–29. Wings of Amazobenna Penny species. 28. Amazobenna reticulata Penny (male); 29. A. pennyi sp. nov. (male). Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632459/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
); genital style narrow at the base and distally broadening with apex truncated, inner face convex in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[285,391,1108,1130]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1893,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,329,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,329,1888]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. Amazobenna reticulata Penny, male: 7. Anal segment, dorsal view; 8. Apex of the anal segment, posterior view; 9. Terminalia, lateral view; 10. Genitalia, ventral view; 11. Anal segment, pygofer, medioventral process, genital style and aedeagus, lateral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: anal seg, anal segment; pyg, pygofer; medven proc, medioventral process; genital sty, genital style; aed, aedeagus, shaf, shaft; flag, flagellum. Scale bars: 16, 19 = 0.3 mm; 17 = 0.2 mm; 18, 20 = 0.3 mm; 21 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632447/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Figs. 9–12</figureCitation>
); apex of the anal segment triangular in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[929,987,1108,1130]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1893,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,329,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,329,1888]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. Amazobenna reticulata Penny, male: 7. Anal segment, dorsal view; 8. Apex of the anal segment, posterior view; 9. Terminalia, lateral view; 10. Genitalia, ventral view; 11. Anal segment, pygofer, medioventral process, genital style and aedeagus, lateral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: anal seg, anal segment; pyg, pygofer; medven proc, medioventral process; genital sty, genital style; aed, aedeagus, shaf, shaft; flag, flagellum. Scale bars: 16, 19 = 0.3 mm; 17 = 0.2 mm; 18, 20 = 0.3 mm; 21 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632447/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); pygofer with posterolateral margin produced in the middle forming an obtuse angle (
<figureCitation box="[601,704,1137,1159]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1893,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,329,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,329,1888]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. Amazobenna reticulata Penny, male: 7. Anal segment, dorsal view; 8. Apex of the anal segment, posterior view; 9. Terminalia, lateral view; 10. Genitalia, ventral view; 11. Anal segment, pygofer, medioventral process, genital style and aedeagus, lateral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: anal seg, anal segment; pyg, pygofer; medven proc, medioventral process; genital sty, genital style; aed, aedeagus, shaf, shaft; flag, flagellum. Scale bars: 16, 19 = 0.3 mm; 17 = 0.2 mm; 18, 20 = 0.3 mm; 21 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632447/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Figs. 9, 11</figureCitation>
), lateral lobe slightly tapered distally and diverging distally in ventral aspect (
<figureCitation box="[232,302,1167,1189]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1893,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,329,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,329,1888]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. Amazobenna reticulata Penny, male: 7. Anal segment, dorsal view; 8. Apex of the anal segment, posterior view; 9. Terminalia, lateral view; 10. Genitalia, ventral view; 11. Anal segment, pygofer, medioventral process, genital style and aedeagus, lateral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: anal seg, anal segment; pyg, pygofer; medven proc, medioventral process; genital sty, genital style; aed, aedeagus, shaf, shaft; flag, flagellum. Scale bars: 16, 19 = 0.3 mm; 17 = 0.2 mm; 18, 20 = 0.3 mm; 21 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632447/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
).............................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Penny" authorityName="Penny" authorityYear="1980" box="[1251,1435,1167,1189]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Amazobenna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulata">
<emphasis box="[1251,1369,1167,1189]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">A. reticulata</emphasis>
Penny
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1049,1336]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="563">
-. Body and legs yellow (
<figureCitation box="[456,530,1196,1218]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1935,1958]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,369,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,369,1871]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 19–23. Amazobenna pennyi sp. nov., holotype: 19. Habitus, lateral view; 20. Head, anterior view; 21. Antenna, lateral view; 22. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 23. Abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 1= 1mm; 2,4 = 0.5mm; 3 = 0.3 mm; 5 = 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632453/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
); wing lacking spot on costal cell, spots at the apex of the medial veins not interconnected basally (
<figureCitation box="[306,377,1225,1247]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,1618,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[188,1398,1618,1955]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28–29. Wings of Amazobenna Penny species. 28. Amazobenna reticulata Penny (male); 29. A. pennyi sp. nov. (male). Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632459/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); genital style long, broad in basal 2/3, narrowing towards the apex with apex round, inner face almost straight and parallel, slightly sinuous near apex in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[795,915,1255,1277]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1454,1477]" captionTargetBox="[198,1403,193,1417]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[198,1403,193,1442]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. Amazobenna pennyi sp. nov., holotype: 24. Male terminalia, lateral view; 25. Male terminalia, posterior view; 26. Anal segment, pygofer, medioventral process and genital style, lateral view. 27. Anal segment, pygofer, medioventral process and genital style, posterior view. Abbreviations: anal seg, anal segment; pyg, pygofer; medven proc, medioventral process; genital sty, genital style. Scale bars: 6,8 = 0.2 mm; 7,9 = 0,3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632457/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Figs. 24–27</figureCitation>
); apex of anal segment trapezoidal in posterior view; pygofer with posterolateral margin slightly sinuous, not forming an obtuse angle (
<figureCitation box="[1004,1120,1284,1306]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1454,1477]" captionTargetBox="[198,1403,193,1417]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[198,1403,193,1442]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. Amazobenna pennyi sp. nov., holotype: 24. Male terminalia, lateral view; 25. Male terminalia, posterior view; 26. Anal segment, pygofer, medioventral process and genital style, lateral view. 27. Anal segment, pygofer, medioventral process and genital style, posterior view. Abbreviations: anal seg, anal segment; pyg, pygofer; medven proc, medioventral process; genital sty, genital style. Scale bars: 6,8 = 0.2 mm; 7,9 = 0,3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632457/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Figs. 24, 26</figureCitation>
), lateral lobe not tapered distally, with parallel inner sides and not diverging distally in ventral aspect (
<figureCitation box="[882,951,1313,1335]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1454,1477]" captionTargetBox="[198,1403,193,1417]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[198,1403,193,1442]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. Amazobenna pennyi sp. nov., holotype: 24. Male terminalia, lateral view; 25. Male terminalia, posterior view; 26. Anal segment, pygofer, medioventral process and genital style, lateral view. 27. Anal segment, pygofer, medioventral process and genital style, posterior view. Abbreviations: anal seg, anal segment; pyg, pygofer; medven proc, medioventral process; genital sty, genital style. Scale bars: 6,8 = 0.2 mm; 7,9 = 0,3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632457/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
)........................ 
